value.0: Brother Idagurdsson is the one to come to if a couple wishes to be wed. He seems to be very good at his job and doesn't ask a lot of questions.
Thorbold wears a large grin and stands proudly, waiting for the woman at his side to finally become his wife.
Clothed in what could be considered a fine dress made from local fur of a white bear, this blushing bride fidgets nervously while sneaking glances at her soon-to-be husband.

Snorri IV is the Spiritual Leader of Howness and High Priest of Helm. He's an elderly man with kind features albeit the harsh life Howness has to offer has wore him down over time. He also seems to be one of the very few more open minded to the thought of outsiders. Nonetheless, his loyalty to the people of Howness is strong and true.
Brother Sigursson works with High Priest Snorri to bless the livestock and takes over the duty entirely when Snorri might have to be away.
Svein is an elderly man who is hardheaded to a fault. Even at his ripe age he continues to work with hix oxen and yaks.

Grimli is one of the few dwarves in Howness who doesn't get too many odd looks given how long he has lived in the settlement. His faith in the Morndinsamman is strong and he likes to make it known. His skills lie in smithing and mining. Because of his skills Grimli begrudgingly aids Olaf Felian at the smithy creating arms and armor out of his strong attachment to the people of Howness. The reasons for Grimli leaving his dwarven hold and family are largely unknown and it seems he wants to keep it that way.
Bjorn is one of the men who are waiting in line for his farm animals to be blessed by the clergy of Helm. He seems alright with waiting as he speaks with Grimli and Thord.

Thord is considered handsome for his age with his golden blonde hair and blue eyes. While waiting his turn for his cow to be blessed by the clergy, he speaks with Grimli and Bjorn. His attention is stolen by his cow every now and then when it tries to be unruly.
While an excellent cook, Brother Skapti is always stuck baking bread...
Brother Vermundsson is a terrible, terrible cook. If you get stale, dry, or otherwise horrible bread it's probably this man's fault.
Brother Liefsson is the man you wish to speak to if you're looking for supplies to survive the harshness of Forrstakkr's wilderness. He makes sure to always be well stocked.
An elderly man, Brother Orpakson keeps mostly to Howness. He keeps in contact with the other clergy in the Thykkvi Monastery mostly through letters.

Dogma of Helm: Never betray your trust. Be vigilant. Stand, wait, and watch carefully. Be fair and diligent in the conduct of your orders. Protect the weak, poor, injured, and young, and do not sacrifice them for others or yourself. Anticipate attacks and be ready. Know your foes. Care for your weapons so they may perform their duties when called upon. Careful planning always defeats rushed actions in the end. Always obey orders, providing those orders follow the dictates of Helm. Demonstrate excellence and purity of loyalty in your role as a guardian and protector.

Dogma of Bahamut: Bahamut is stern and very disapproving of evil. He brooks no excuses for evil acts. In spite of this, he is among the most compassionate beings in the multiverse. He has limitless empathy for the downtrodden, the dispossessed,and the helpless. He urges his followers to promote the cause of good, but prefers to let beings fight their own battles when they can. To Bahamut, it is better to offer information, healing, or a (temporary) safe refuge rather than to take others' burden upon oneself.
